  <head>
    <meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8">
    <title> Sweating_case_sheet_part</title>
    <link href="Case_sheet_styles.css" id="light-styles" rel="stylesheet">
    <link href="Case_sheet_styles_dark.css" id="dark-styles" rel="alternate stylesheet"

      title="dark">
    <script src="https://www.youtube.com/iframe_api"></script>
  </head>
  <body> <button id="theme-toggle" title="Toggle dark mode"> Dark Mode</button>
    <div class="General">
      <h3>1ST COMPLAINT: EXCESSIVE SWEATING</h3>
      <!-- S: Site -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>S</strong>:
            Site</span>
          <ul>
            <li><b>GENERALIZED (all over):</b> </li>
            <ul>
              <li><span class="endocrine">Endocrine
                  (Thyroid, Menopause)</span>, </li>
              <li><span class="infectious">Infection</span>,&nbsp;<span class="oncology"></span></li>
              <li><span class="oncology">Malignancy</span>,&nbsp;<span class="pharmacology"></span></li>
              <li><span class="pharmacology">Medications</span>,&nbsp;<span class="neurology"></span></li>
              <li><span class="neurology">Autonomic disorders</span>,&nbsp;<span

                  class="cvs"></span></li>
              <li><span class="cvs">CVS</span></li>
            </ul>
            <li><b>LOCALIZED / FOCAL:</b>
              <ul>
                <li class="derma">Palms, Soles, Axillae</li>
                <ul>
                  <li class="derma">1` Focal Hyperhidrosis</li>
                </ul>
                <li class="cns">Face (while eating) </li>
                <ul>
                  <li class="cns">Gustatory sweating (Frey's Syndrome)</li>
                </ul>
                <li class="neurology">Unilateral facial </li>
                <ul>
                  <li class="neurology">Horner syndrome</li>
                </ul>
                <li class="surgical">Compensatory sweating </li>
                <ul>
                  <li class="surgical">Post-sympathectomy</li>
                </ul>
              </ul>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"Where on your body do you notice the sweating the
          most? Is it all over, or in specific places like your hands, feet, or
          armpits?"</span></div>
      <!-- O: Onset -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>O</strong>:
            Onset</span>
          <ul>
            <li>Since puberty
              <ul>
                <li>1` focal hyperhidrosis</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>Recent&nbsp;
              <ul>
                <li>Secondary hyperhidrosis</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"When did you first notice this excessive sweating?
          Was it a sudden change or has it been gradual?"</span></div>
      <!-- D: Duration -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>D</strong>:
            Duration</span> </div>
        <span class="verbal">"How long has this been a problem for you?"</span></div>
      <!-- A/R: Aggravating / Relieving Factors -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>A/R</strong>:
            Aggravating &amp; Relieving Factors</span> </div>
        <span class="verbal">"Does anything seem to trigger the sweating, like
          stress or certain foods?"</span></div>
      <!-- C: Character (THE KEY DIFFERENTIATOR) -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>C</strong>:
            Character (Timing &amp; Triggers)</span>
          <ul>
            <li class="oncology infectious endocrine emergency"><b>NIGHT SWEATS</b>
              <ul>
                <li><b>"Drenching" sweats?</b> (Requiring changing of clothes or
                  bedsheets) -&gt; This is a B-Symptom.</li>
                <li>hot flushes? -&gt; <b class="endocrine gynob">Menopause</b>
                  OR <b class="endocrine">Male hypogonadism</b></li>
                <li>Associated with alcohol use? -&gt; <b class="psych">Alcohol-induced
                    sweating</b></li>
                <li>Associated with specific foods? -&gt; <b class="gi">GERD</b>
                  or gustatory sweating</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li class="General"><b>DAYTIME SWEATING</b>
              <ul>
                <li>with eating? -&gt; <b class="cns">Gustatory sweating</b></li>
                <li>Constant hot and sweaty? -&gt; <b class="endocrine">Hyperthyroidism</b></li>
              </ul>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"This is a key question: when does the sweating
          happen? Is it mainly at night, during the day, or in specific
          situations?"</span></div>
      <!-- R: Radiation -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>R</strong>:
            Radiation</span> </div>
        <span class="verbal">(Not applicable)</span></div>
      <!-- A: Associated Symptoms -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>A</strong>:
            Associated Symptoms</span>
          <ul>
            <li class="oncology infectious">CONSTITUTIONAL ("B SYMPTOMS")
              <ul>
                <li class="oncology infectious">Unexplained Fever</li>
                <ul>
                  <li class="oncology infectious"><b class="infectious">Infection
                      (TB, HIV, Endocarditis)</b></li>
                </ul>
                <li class="oncology infectious">Drenching Night Sweats</li>
                <li class="oncology">Unexplained Weight Loss</li>
                <ul>
                  <li class="oncology"><b class="oncology">Leukemia</b>, <b class="infectious">TB</b></li>
                </ul>
                <li class="oncology">Lymph node swelling ?</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li class="endocrine">ENDOCRINE
              <ul>
                <li class="endocrine cvs">Palpitations, anxiety, tremor,
                  diarrhea, heat intolerance -&gt; <b class="endocrine">Hyperthyroidism</b></li>
                <li class="endocrine cvs emergency">Episodic headache,
                  palpitations, and sweating -&gt; <b class="endocrine emergency">Pheochromocytoma
                    Triad</b></li>
                <li class="endocrine">Hot flushes, menstrual changes -&gt; <b class="endocrine gynob">Menopause</b></li>
                <li class="endocrine">Sweating during hunger spells -&gt; <b class="endocrine">Hypoglycemia</b></li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li class="cvs">CARDIOVASCULAR
              <ul>
                <li class="cvs emergency">Associated with chest pain or
                  shortness of breath -&gt; <b class="cvs emergency">Acute
                    Coronary Syndrome</b></li>
                <li class="cvs">Orthopnea, paroxysmal nocturnal dyspnea -&gt; <b

                    class="cvs">Heart Failure</b></li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li class="infectious">INFECTIOUS
              <ul>
                <li class="infectious respiratory">Chronic cough, hemoptysis,
                  travel/contact history -&gt; <b class="infectious">Tuberculosis
                    (TB)</b></li>
                <li class="infectious">High-risk behaviors, other infections
                  -&gt; <b class="infectious">HIV</b></li>
                <li class="infectious">New heart murmur, IV drug use -&gt; <b class="infectious">Endocarditis</b></li>
                <li class="infectious">Epstein-Barr virus (infectious
                  mononucleosis)</li>
                <li class="infectious">Malaria, histoplasmosis,
                  coccidioidomycosis (travel history)</li>
                <li class="infectious">Opportunistic infections (Pneumocystis,
                  Mycobacterium avium)</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li class="pharmacology">MEDICATION-INDUCED (Most common secondary
              cause)
              <ul>
                <li class="pharmacology"><b>Psychiatric meds:</b> SSRIs,
                  tricyclics, antipsychotics</li>
                <li class="pharmacology"><b>Pain meds:</b> Opioids, NSAIDs</li>
                <li class="pharmacology"><b>Antibiotics:</b> Cephalosporins,
                  quinolones, antivirals</li>
                <li class="pharmacology"><b>Endocrine meds:</b> Steroids,
                  thyroid medications, insulin, glipizide</li>
                <li class="pharmacology"><b>Neurology meds:</b>
                  Acetylcholinesterase inhibitors (donepezil, benztropine)</li>
                <li class="pharmacology"><b>Withdrawal:</b> Alcohol, caffeine,
                  benzodiazepines</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li class="neurology">NEUROLOGICAL / AUTONOMIC
              <ul>
                <li class="neurology">Autonomic dysfunction, dysautonomia,
                  multiple system atrophy</li>
                <li class="neurology">Parkinson's disease, multiple sclerosis,
                  stroke, spinal cord injury</li>
                <li class="neurology">Peripheral neuropathy, small fiber
                  neuropathy</li>
                <li class="neurology">Horner syndrome (unilateral facial
                  sweating)</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li class="respiratory">SLEEP DISORDERS
              <ul>
                <li class="respiratory">Obstructive sleep apnea, restless legs
                  syndrome</li>
                <li class="respiratory">Nightmares, night terrors, REM sleep
                  behavior disorder</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li class="gi">GASTROINTESTINAL
              <ul>
                <li class="gi">GERD (gastroesophageal reflux disease)</li>
                <li class="gi">Waking with bitter taste in mouth</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li class="psych">PSYCHIATRIC / BEHAVIORAL
              <ul>
                <li class="psych">Panic attacks, anxiety disorders, PTSD,
                  depression</li>
                <li class="psych">Obesity, high-fat/high-sugar diet</li>
                <li clarheumaticsych">Alcohol use, smoking (&gt;3 drinks/day)</li>
              </ul>
            </li>rheumatic
            <li class="rheurheumaticTOIMMUNE / RHEUMATOLOGIC
              <ul>
                <li class="rheum">Sarcoidosis, rheumatoid arthritis, lupus</li>
                <li class="rheum">Sj&ouml;gren's syndrome</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"Along with the sweating, have you experienced any
          other symptoms like fever, weight loss, or palpitations?"</span></div>
      <!-- P: Progression -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>P</strong>:
            Progression</span> </div>
        <span class="verbal">"Has the sweating been getting worse over time?"</span></div>
      <!-- P: Pattern -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>P</strong>:
            Pattern</span> </div>
        <span class="verbal">"Is there any pattern to the sweating throughout
          the day or month?"</span></div>
      <!-- E: Effect on life -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>E</strong>:
            Effect on Life</span>
          <ul>
            <li>Social embarrassment / avoidance</li>
            <li>Need to change clothes frequently</li>
            <li>Disrupted sleep</li>
            <li>Difficulty with tasks (e.g., gripping objects if palmar)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"How has this sweating been impacting your life?
          For example, your work, social activities, or sleep?"</span></div>
      <!-- R: Red Flags -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>R</strong>:
            Red Flags</span>
          <ul>
            <li class="oncology infectious emergency">The "B-Symptoms":
              Drenching night sweats, unexplained fever, significant weight
              loss.</li>
            <li class="cvs emergency">Sweating associated with <b><u>chest </u><u>pain
                  </u></b>or severe shortness of breath.</li>
            <li class="endocrine emergency"><b><u>Episodic </u></b>sweating
              with severe headaches and palpitations.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"I'm just going to summarize the key warning signs
          I'm looking for."</span></div>
      <!-- S: Scale -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>S</strong>:
            Severity / Bother Scale</span> </div>
        <span class="verbal">"On a scale of 1 to 10, how much does this sweating
          bother you and interfere with your life?"</span></div>
      <span class="verbal"></span> </div>
